and lists similarities and differences,

30
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:54,780
then explains how to tell them apart.

31
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:58,060
So if you can be more detailed in what you're asking for,

32
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:02,500
then the chatbot will better understand what you're looking for and try to respond accordingly.

33
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:08,080
Another general suggestion is to break down your task into a sequence of subtasks.

34
00:02:08,420 --> 00:02:11,760
For instance, you can ask what's the difference between these two types of dogs

35
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:15,280
and give it a list of steps that you might have taken to answer this question yourself.

36
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:19,760
First, review reference material, then list out similarities and differences,

37
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:22,700
And finally, suggest how to tell them apart.

38
00:02:26,620 --> 00:02:27,680
And let's see what you might get.

39
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:34,840
And you can see at the top, it says, searched two sites,

40
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:37,860
meaning that it took those two web links that were provided

41
00:02:38,540 --> 00:02:40,720
and looked through those in order for it to answer the question.

42
00:02:41,480 --> 00:02:44,660
And notice that there is a logical sequence to the subtasks.

43
00:02:45,020 --> 00:02:47,800
The earlier tasks involve research and gathering information.

44
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:53,040
Those come before the later tasks that involve using that information to draw conclusions.

45
00:02:53,940 --> 00:02:57,840
And you can also describe how you want the output to be organized or formatted,

46
